Sentencas: A detailed mathematical model is developed and is used to study the significance of thermal radiation on cell performance.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: While transport equations are solved in a 2D-axisymmetric domain, radiation is modeled in 3D.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It is found that radiation plays a significant role in heat transfer to a degree that without it no physically meaningful simulation can be obtained.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A sensitivity analysis is performed to study the effect of the emissivity of various surfaces involved in radiation heat transfer.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The emissivity of the cell surface has the highest impact on its temperature distribution, and in general larger emissivity values result in lower temperature gradients.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The 25 C temperature gradient along the cell's active length became less at higher emmisvities.
Titulo: Significance of radiative heat transfer in modeling a tubular micro-solid oxide fuel cell
